### Before reporting an issue

- [X] I have searched existing issues
- [X] I have reproduced the issue with the latest release

### Area

account/api

### Describe the bug

When we run the traffic test we have seen memory increment, we have noticed it was due to the LinkedHashMap in PathCache https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/blob/bfce612641a70e106b20b136431f0e4046b5c37f/adapters/oidc/adapter-core/src/main/java/org/keycloak/adapters/authorization/PathCache.java#L56

However, as per JDK documentation LinkedHashMap is not thread-safe and hence we are seeing that over a period of time the entries in cache keeps growing thus leading to memory leak issue. 

### Version

17.0.1

### Expected behavior

Should not increase the memory 

### Actual behavior

Noticed more memory utilization and leading to memory leak issue.

### How to Reproduce?

Below sample code can help to understand the issue 

import java.util.Collections;
import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.LinkedHashMap;
import java.util.Map;

public class LinkedHashMapEntryRemovalTest {

    // Refers to the max size of the map following which
    // the removal takes place of the eldest entry
    private static final int MAX = 100;
    // Creating the linked hashmap and implementing
    // removeEldestEntry() to MAX size
    Map<Integer, String> li_hash_map = new LinkedHashMap<Integer, String>(16, 0.75f, true) {
        protected boolean removeEldestEntry(Map.Entry<Integer, String> eldest) {
            System.out.println("Removing key = " + eldest.getKey() + " :: size =" + size());
            return size() > MAX;
        }
    };


    /* with this code i can see no incremetn in the size
    Map<Integer, String> li_hash_map = Collections.synchronizedMap(new LinkedHashMap<Integer, String>(16, 0.75f, true) {
        protected boolean removeEldestEntry(Map.Entry<Integer, String> eldest) {
            System.out.println("Removing key = " + eldest.getKey() + " :: size =" + size());
            return size() > MAX;
        }
    });*/


    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new LinkedHashMapEntryRemovalTest();
    }

    public LinkedHashMapEntryRemovalTest() {
        Thread t = new Thread(new Runnable() {

            @Override
            public void run() {
                int i = 0;
                for (;;) {
                    i++;
                    addValue(i);
                    try {
                        Thread.sleep(100);
                    } catch (Exception e) {
                        // TODO: handle exception
                    }
                }
            }
        }, "TestLinkedHashMap");

        Thread t2 = new Thread(new Runnable() {

            @Override
            public void run() {
                int i = 100000;
                for (;;) {
                    i++;
                    addValue(i);
                    try {
                        Thread.sleep(100);
                    } catch (Exception e) {
                        // TODO: handle exception
                    }
                }
            }
        }, "TestLinkedHashMap2");


        t.start();
        t2.start();
    }

    private void addValue(int i) {
        li_hash_map.put(i, "Num" + i);
    }

}


